      <h2 class="text-3xl font-medium mb-6">Fuse Box, Consumer Unit & Circuit Breaker Considerations</h2>
      <p class="mb-6">
        When planning to install a new plug socket, it's vital to consider the role of your fuse box, consumer unit, and circuit breaker in maintaining electrical safety. The consumer unit—often found near the front door or in a utility area—manages all the circuits in your property. Before any electrical work begins, a professional electrician will always ensure the power is switched off at the consumer unit, isolating the correct circuit breaker to prevent accidental shocks or power surges.
      </p>
      <p>
        If you're adding a new plug socket or several new sockets, your existing fuse box or consumer unit may need to be assessed to confirm it can handle the extra load. This is especially important for high-demand appliances or if your current system uses older fuses rather than modern micro circuit breakers. Upgrading your consumer unit not only supports additional sockets but also brings your installation in line with the latest building regulations and electrical safety standards. Always consult a qualified electrician to ensure your sockets are installed safely, your system is correctly wired, and your home remains protected.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

