          The overall cost of installing a new plug socket can vary depending on what's hidden behind your walls. Both solid wall and stud wall installations may require tools like a hammer action drill or pad saw to create space for the mounting box. However, if there are hidden pipes or cables, the job becomes more complex and labour costs can increase.
        </p>
        <p>
          A professional electrician will use a pipe and cable detector to scan for any hidden obstacles before cutting into the wall, helping to avoid costly damage and ensuring a safe installation. If you're planning to add more sockets, it's wise to consider not just the price of the socket itself, but also the potential for extra labour if hidden pipes are discovered. By planning ahead and working with a qualified electrician, you can save money by preventing unexpected repairs and ensuring the mounting box fits snugly without damaging existing wiring or plumbing. Factoring in these considerations helps keep your overall cost under control and ensures your new plug socket is installed safely and efficiently.
        </p>
